question: Will 'Shazam! Fury of the Gods' gross more than $35 million domestically on its opening weekend?
description:
'Shazam! Fury of the Gods' (2023) is an upcoming American Superhero film directed by David F. Sandberg. It is it is the sequel to Shazam! (2019) and the 12th installment in the DC Extended Universe (DCEU). It is scheduled for theatrical release in the USA on March 17, 2023.

This is a market on how much ‘Shazam! Fury of the Gods' will gross domestically on its opening weekend. The “Domestic Weekend” tab on https://www.boxofficemojo.com/title/tt10151854/ will be used to resolve this market once the values for the opening weekend (Mar 17 - 19) are final (i.e. not studio estimates).

This market will resolve to "Yes" if ‘Shazam! Fury of the Gods’ grosses more than $35,000,000 on its opening weekend. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

Opening weekend is defined as the first Friday, Saturday, and Sunday of the film's release. Please note, this market will resolve according to the Box Office Mojo number under Domestic Weekend for the 3-day weekend, regardless of whether domestic refers to only the USA, or to USA and Canada, etc.

If there is no final data available by April 3, 2023, 11:59:59 PM ET, another credible resolution source will be chosen.

events.title: 'Shazam! Fury of the Gods' opening weekend
events.description: This is a market group over how much 'Shazam! Fury of the Gods' gross domestically on its opening weekend.

question: Arbitrum token FDV >$5b one week after launch?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if the Fully Diluted Valuation of Arbitrum's token is above $5,000,000,000 1 week after launch. Otherwise, the market will resolve to "No."

"1 week after launch" is defined as exactly 7 days (168 hours) after the token is claimable. The Arbitrum Foundation has currently announced the token will be claimable on block https://etherscan.io/block/countdown/16890400.

Fully Diluted Valuation (FDV) = Current Price x Max Supply

The resolution source for this market is a consensus of highly liquid sources of $ARB's FDV 1 week after launch. If Arbitrum doesn't launch a token by December 31, 2023, 11:59:59 PM ET, this market will resolve to 50-50.

question: Will Arbitrum's token address have a letter in it?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if the Arbitrum token address on the Arbitrum network has a letter in it. Otherwise, the market will resolve to "No."

Only characters after the "0x" count for this market. Both lowercase and capital letters count for this market (a-f, A-F).

If no Arbitrum token address on the Arbitrum network is available by April 30, 2023, 11:59:59 PM ET, this market will resolve 50-50.

The primary resolution source for this market is official information from the Arbitrum network, however a consensus of credible reporting may suffice.

question: Formula 1: Will Red Bull collect the most points of any constructor at the 2023 Saudi Arabian Grand Prix?
description:
This is a market on whether the Red Bull constructor team will collect the most points at the 2023 Saudi Arabian Grand Prix, a Formula 1 racing event that is scheduled to take place over 50 laps of the 6.175 km Jeddah Corniche Circuit in Jeddah, Saudi Arabia on March 19, 2023.

Constructor teams are awarded the same points won by the drivers who race in their cars. If, for example, the drivers earn 25 and 18 points, respectively, their constructor team will be awarded 43 points, which are the points won by both drivers combined.

This market will resolve to “Yes” if Oracle Red Bull Racing collects more points than any other constructor team at the 2023 Saudi Arabian Grand Prix. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

If for any reason the 2023 Saudi Arabian Grand Prix is rescheduled to a different time and date on or before April 2, 2023, the same market conditions will apply. If the race is rescheduled to a time and date after April 2, 2023, this market will resolve to 50-50.

description:

question: Will 'Shazam! Fury of the Gods' gross more than $25 million domestically on its opening weekend?
description:
'Shazam! Fury of the Gods' (2023) is an upcoming American Superhero film directed by David F. Sandberg. It is the sequel to Shazam! (2019) and the 12th installment in the DC Extended Universe (DCEU). It is scheduled for theatrical release in the USA on March 17, 2023.

This is a market on how much ‘Shazam! Fury of the Gods' will gross domestically on its opening weekend. The “Domestic Weekend” tab on https://www.boxofficemojo.com/title/tt10151854/ will be used to resolve this market once the values for the opening weekend (Mar 17 - 19) are final (i.e. not studio estimates).

This market will resolve to "Yes" if ‘Shazam! Fury of the Gods’ grosses more than $25,000,000 on its opening weekend. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

Opening weekend is defined as the first Friday, Saturday, and Sunday of the film's release. Please note, this market will resolve according to the Box Office Mojo number under Domestic Weekend for the 3-day weekend, regardless of whether domestic refers to only the USA, or to USA and Canada, etc.

If there is no final data available by April 3, 2023, 11:59:59 PM ET, another credible resolution source will be chosen.
